          Appendix 3  13 
the M&E system for the SEDP is to review and design a suitable computerized M&E system for 
the SEDP. This system will cover the SEDP programs and projects and will be capable of 
covering the entire country down to the district level. Part of the work under this TA will be for 
the  project  team  to  review  the  existing  M&E  system  and  to  examine  the  potential  for 
computerizing it. For this purpose, the project team will need the services of an IT expert who 
will provide advice and inputs for the design and development of an computerized M&E system. 
The IT expert will:  

(i)  review the IT aspects of the existing M&E system; 
(ii)  help the international M&E consultant with the conceptual framework and details 
for automating the M&E system; 
(iii)  advise the international M&E consultant on the options for computerizing the 
revised M&E system for the SEDP; 
(iv)  help  the  international  M&E  consultant  draw  up  the  specifications  for  the 
computerized SEDP M&E system and related systems; 
(v)  help with the design and development of a computerized M&E system, including 
an online web portal for the SEDP M&E system; 
(vi)  oversee the implementation and trial testing of the computerized M&E system; 
(vii)  be responsible for the smooth operation and functionality of the computerized 
M&E system when it is commissioned; 
(viii)  review and prepare detailed reports on possible adjustments needed for the 
computerized M&E system; 
(ix)  prepare  a  training  program,  training  materials,  and  other  training  support 
documents for the computerized M&E system; 
(x)  carry out appropriate technical training for agency officials on the use of the 
computerized M&E system;  
(xi)  prepare and submit progress and performance reports to project management on 
the development and use of the computerized M&E system; and 
(xii)  work closely with the team leader and international M&E consultant to review and 
identify  improvements  to  the  computerized  system  during  the  first  year  of 
operation.
